      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Some miners probably about 15-20% of the hashrate consider all dependencies as a group, so your argument of the fee being irrelevant doesn't hold compeltely.\n\nYou're still not answering my core question, which is why do you think refusing to make a transaction at all would be an improvement?\n",
